 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATO'S `CLOBBA SLOBBA' NONSENSE &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (Provocative Commentary) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By ROBERT FISK, The Independent of London &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BELGRADE _ Instead of admitting the truth about the current
Kosovo conflict, our leaders have consistently lied to us. It has
all gone horribly wrong.
</P>
<P>
   Indeed, if the initial objectives are recalled, then we have
already lost this war. And it is not only the tragedy of Biblical
proportions on the Balkan mountainsides that proves the futility of
what we have done.
</P>
<P>
   Almost two weeks ago, we thought we had gone to war to save the
Kosovo Albanians. Now it turns out that we are at war to save NATO.
</P>
<P>
   The 12,000 soldiers who were meant to look after the Kosovo
Albanians are now doing just that _ but in the wrong country,
Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
   The Serb civilians of Kosovo, whom they were also meant to
protect, are now being bombed by us. The destabilization of the
southern Balkans, which we went to war to prevent, is now well
underway... &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (EDITORS: Note 300-word OPTIONAL TRIM at 875. Total uncut is
1,450) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MOVED AS BC-WE'VE-LOST-FOOLISH-WAR-875&AMP;add-INDEPENDENT-NYTSF &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BOMBS AND BOMBAST: WAKE UP, 1999 NEVILLE CHAMBERLAINS! &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (Pithy Commentary) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By DAVID AARONOVITCH, The Independent of London &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LONDON _ We pampered Westerners are all very martial as long as
we are only dropping ordnance from the sky.
</P>
<P>
   The air is now thick with the stink of attitudinizing. Every
columnist, reporter, letter-writer, pub bore and backbencher knows
what should have been done, and what ought to be done now.
</P>
<P>
   What I believe about Kosovo _ that we had little alternative but
to intervene, and that we should now begin to deploy an army
charged with winning it back for its dispossessed people _ is not
the consequence of deep strategic and military insight. It is,
rather, a product of conscience allied to a deep worry about what
would happen elsewhere were we to fail this test... &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (EDITORS: Note 325-word OPTIONAL TRIM at 600. Total uncut is
1,175) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MOVED AS
BC-ARMCHAIR-WARMONGERS-OPED-600&AMP;add-INDEPENDENT-NYTSF &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
