<P>
   &UR; YK2 BABIES: WHAT WILL THEIR FUTURE BE? &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (NOTE: Friday, April 9, a Millennium baby will be conceived) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By GEOFFREY LEAN, The Independent of London &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   This Friday, somewhere in the world, a historic baby will start
its journey into life. For then _ the 266 days of an average
pregnancy away from the turn of the year _ the first child of the
new millennium will be conceived.
</P>
<P>
   No one will know who or where it is, as it grows towards its
date with destiny spinning gently in its mother's womb. It may be
born rich or poor, male or female, black, brown, yellow or white _
in circumstances as diverse as the wide world itself.
</P>
<P>
   The real millennium baby is most likely to be born with no clock
in sight, with no record of its time of birth. It may not even live
long enough to be given a name. For there are nine chances in 10
that it will arrive in the Third World, rather than in the West _
and four in 10 that it will be born into extreme poverty. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (EDITORS: This story stands in 475 words. Total uncut is
1,250.) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MOVED AS BC-WOE-BABIES-MILLENNIUM-475&AMP;add-INDEPENDENT-NYTSF &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BODY AND SOUL: A DAY OF RECKONING WITH GOD'S MUSCLE MEN &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By ANN TRENEMAN, The Independent of London &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   James Henderson is the largest man I have ever met. He is 6-ft.,
5-in. and weighs 390 lbs., but those statistics cannot do justice
to his extreme gigantism. He is a fridge-freezer with skin.
</P>
<P>
   He has come to east London from Texas to tell me what it is like
to be a Muscle Man for God.
</P>
<P>
   James, plus some 25 others, are members of the ``Power Team.''
In between breaking walls of concrete, bending steel bars, snapping
baseball bats and ripping up phone books, they talk about the Lord.
The whole thing is a bit like evangelical wrestling... &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (950 words) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
