<P>
   &UR; WEST ALARMED BY PLANS TO BURY CHERNOBYL REACTOR &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By STEVE CONNOR, The Independent of London &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   An ambitious plan to bury the crippled Chernobyl nuclear reactor
in a giant hole more than half a mile deep has been proposed by a
group of Ukrainian research centers. Western experts have reacted
with alarm to the idea... &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (475 words) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MOVED AS BC-CHERNOBYL-`GRAVE'-INDEPENDENT-NYTSF &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OUR DUTY TO CARE: REFUGEES ARE MORE THAN `COLLATERAL DAMAGE' &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (Editorial) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By THE EDITORIAL BOARD OF THE INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Modern Europe _ that civilized territory _ watches wretched,
dirty and hopeless refugees fight for a loaf of bread even as eight
million dollars' worth of cruise missiles explode on nearby
Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
   NATO is indeed degrading the military resources of President
Slobodan Milosevic, but our failure adequately to support the
refugees degrades and demeans us all.
</P>
<P>
   One of the frightening euphemisms of modern warfare, brought
into vogue in the Gulf War, is ``collateral damage.'' The refugees
from Kosovo are the collateral damage of this NATO action, and we
must do whatever we can to support them. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (725 words) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MOVED AS BC-CARE-FOR-KOSOVARS-OPED-INDEPENDENT-NYTSF &LR;  &QC; 
