East Texas' Senate District 3. The district, which runs from north
of Houston to Tyler and east to the Louisiana line, is at the top
of the Democrats' target list. Winning it back could reverse the
16-15 majority Republicans enjoy over Democrats. (McNeely, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Under current state policies, being
gay or lesbian does not exclude a person from being a foster
parent. State case workers generally will attain a handle on facets
of a foster parent's personal life before assigning a child for
foster care. But sexual orientation alone will not disqualify an
applicant. Nor should it. (John Young is opinion page editor of the
Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
