call Don Munday on the Star's News Desk at (816) 234-4714.
INJUR: Children's Mercy Hospital releases Kansas City's first
neighborhood by neighborhood study of childhood injuries. Rates of
death and severe injury varied by a factor of 10 in certain
neighborhoods in the Jackson County portion of Kansas City. Guns
and automobiles were the leading causes of death. The hospital
hopes the study will be a first step toward grassroots efforts to
make neighborhoods safer for children. Graphics showing the
neighborhoods with the highest rates of child injury and death,
most frequent cases of death and injury, photo of doc who led the
study and of a playground littered with glass and syringes at
Troost Park. Alan Bavley. 35-40.
