are working on laws that would provide legal immunity to businesses
with Y2K problems. That outrages consumer groups. Finn Bullers. 26.
FORCE: Kosovo on top of Iraq has meant our smaller Air Force is
being stretched. We're running low on cruise missiles and even
moving refugees has slowed things like deploying our attack
helicopters. Scott Canon. 30.
MGE: It's been two years since gas-bill shock and other troubles,
and MGE says its house is in order. Regulators and consumer groups
aren't so sure. A progress report. Steve Everly
PLANET: Planet Hollywood now appears to be an unlikely prime tenant
in the proposed Centertainment District development. Jennifer Mann
