   SOC-REVOLUTION (Undated) _ The Revolution are regrouping for
their MLS home opener against D.C. United Saturday. Edwin Gorter
will return from suspension and Giovanni Savarese is almost over a
bruised ankle and shin. By Frank Dell'Apa.
</P>
<P>
   BBA SHAUGHNESSY-COLUMN (Anaheim, Calif.) _ Mo Vaughn toiled for
10 seasons for the Red Sox. He knows all about curses. Now he plays
for the Angels, another franchise that seems to have angered the
diamond gods. By Dan Shaughnessy.
</P>
<P>
   HOLLEY-COLUMN (Boston) -- Thirty years and three weeks after
Bill Russell played his final game for the Celtics, he'll be be
honored in a tribute in Boston. By Michael Holley.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MASTER'S TOURNAMENT (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GLF-ROUGH (Augusta, Ga.) _ Here at Augusta National Golf Club
the rough _ though smooth _ is still called ``rough'' by the
smooth-talkers. And tradition is said to tremble. By Michael
Madden. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   GLF-DUVAL (Augusta, Ga.) _ David Duval is quiet, introspective.
He is now also golf's best player, in the middle of an astonishing
streak. By Joe Concannon. 880 words.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-WOODS (Augusta, Ga.) _ That ``boat load of emotion'' that
Fred Couples mentioned seems far away from Tiger Woods, so in
control here. By Michael Madden. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
