<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HEARST-NEWS-BUDGET-HNS </SLUG>
  
 Thursday, April 8, 1999    
 Editors      The Hearst News Service will file the following
stories for Friday and Sunday. If you have questions, please call
Susie McBee or Tim Spence at 202-298-6920.    (The ``HNS'' tag
appears in all sluglines.)   
<TEXT>
<P>
   For Friday:
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Somebody should tell the Supreme
Court that a purse is more than just a ``container.'' It is a
woman's very identity. The justices stupidly ruled this week that a
warrantless search of a car passenger's pocket is unconstitutional
but a purse, which they labeled a container, is fair game. By
MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
<P>
   For Sunday:
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-INTERNET (Washington) _ Just as television has brought
the Vietnam War and other conflicts into living rooms worldwide,
the Internet is bringing an even more intimate view of the struggle
over Kosovo to people around the globe. For the first time in
history, a war is being waged in cyberspace. By MARK HELM.
</P>
</TEXT>
