<TEXT>
<P>
   The premiere of ``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom Menace'' is
a little over a month away.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's just another film,'' you say. ``What's the big deal?''
</P>
<P>
   Think again:
</P>
<P>
   -- The buzz has been so intense that the studio has bumped up
the premiere from May 21 to May 19.
</P>
<P>
   -- Thousands of fans paid money just to see the trailer!
</P>
<P>
   -- Some critics think it will be bigger than ``Titanic.''
</P>
<P>
   .............OO..............OO...............
</P>
<P>
   .......OO.....OO.....OO.....OO.....OO.........
</P>
<P>
   .........OO....OO....OO....OO....OO...........
</P>
<P>
   ...........OO...OO...OO...OO...OO.............
</P>
<P>
   .............OO..OO..OO..OO..OO...............
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times Syndicate's STAR WARS COUNTDOWN package can
help guide your readers to the biggest cultural event this side of
the Millennium.
</P>
<P>
   .............OO..OO..OO..OO..OO...............
</P>
<P>
   ...........OO...OO...OO...OO...OO.............
</P>
<P>
   .........OO....OO....OO....OO....OO...........
</P>
<P>
   .......OO.....OO.....OO.....OO.....OO.........
</P>
<P>
   .............OO..............OO...............
</P>
<P>
   STAR WARS COUNTDOWN is a multipart package of interviews with
the film's stars and some fun features _ with art available
electronically.
</P>
<P>
   --------------------EXCLUSIVE OFFER--------------------
</P>
<P>
   Buy the multipart STAR WARS COUNTDOWN package for $500 _ or get
it FREE by subscribing to Ian Spelling's INSIDE SCI-FI column,
which is distributed by The New York Times Syndicate.
</P>
<P>
   -------------------------------------------------------
</P>
<P>
   Ian's first interview is with Samuel L. Jackson, who plays Mace
Windu. The story and art can be sent to you IMMEDIATELY for review.
Call 888-269-8796.
</P>
<P>
   FROM THE INTERVIEW:
</P>
<P>
   ``I love the genre,'' Jackson says over lunch at the Four
Seasons Hotel in New York. ``I wanted to be in a `Star Wars' movie.
So the next time I was asked (which director he wished to work
with), I said, `I would love to work with George Lucas.'
</P>
<P>
   `` ... (On the set) some guy would come over to me and he'd open
a case,'' says Jackson, who recalls seeing the original ``Star
Wars'' movie on its opening day in 1977. ``Inside were, like, nine
lightsabers, and he'd say, `Choose yours.' I'd be there
hyperventilating. I'd say, `Oh, I'll take that one.' It was very
cool.''
</P>
<P>
   UP NEXT:
</P>
<P>
   ``STAR WARS FEVER''
</P>
<P>
   (EDS: This feature can be easily localized.)
</P>
<P>
   How are die-hard ``Star Wars'' fans occupying themselves as they
wait for the premiere of ``The Phantom Menace''?
</P>
<P>
   Fernando DeRosa, a 22-year-old college student from Suffern,
N.Y., dresses up as the character Boba Fett and attends sci-fi
conventions.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dressing up as Fett, going to conventions, talking to people
about the character and how I made the costume, and posing for
photos with kids really helped me come out of my shell,'' he says.
</P>
<P>
   The costume, fashioned from assorted pieces of fabric, plastic
and metal, as well as parts purchased online, took two years to
assemble and cost nearly $2,000.
</P>
<P>
   Derek Bruner, an electrician from Houston, Texas, toils away on
``Star Wars _ The Living Story,'' an Internet-based saga set six
years before ``Star Wars.'' Brunner's Web page has had 15,000 hits
since its debut in August 1997!
</P>
<P>
   FOR MORE INFORMATION ABOUT THE PACKAGE ... call toll-free
888-269-8796 to connect to a New York Times Syndicate sales
executive near you.
</P>
<P>
   Thank you.
</P>
<P>
   _ The New York Times Syndicate.
