   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   US-CHINA _ WASHINGTON _ The United States and China have been
unable to resolve differences on eliminating Chinese trade
barriers, an administration official said today. That makes it
unlikely that U.S. approval for China's membership in the World
Trade Organization will come during Premier Zhu Rongji's visit.
Meanwhile, Clinton holds a press conference with Zhu. (Deans, Cox
News Service).
</P>
<P>
   '
