<HEADLINE>
KOSOVO CONFLICT ON THE WEB 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For release Sunday, April 11)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 Hearst Newspapers  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following is a list of some of the Internet Web sites
providing information on the conflict in Kosovo:
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   www.state.gov/www/regions/eur/kosovo_hp.html
</P>
<P>
   _ Special section of the State Department Web page on the Kosovo
conflict. Provides press releases, maps and fact sheets on the
region.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   www.nato.int
</P>
<P>
   _ Official NATO Web site. Provides press releases, maps and
videos of NATO air attacks against targets.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   www.gov.yu
</P>
<P>
   _ Official site of the Republic of Yugoslavia. Provides press
releases, maps, pictures and history of the country.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   www.serbia-info.com
</P>
<P>
   _ Official Province of Serbia Web site with information on
Serbian culture and history.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   web.eunet.ch/government/ABAZA.html
</P>
<P>
   _ Official web site of the Republic of Kosovo, providing history
and culture of ethnic Albanians in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   www.zik.com
</P>
<P>
   _ Web site for the Kosovo Liberation Army.
</P>
