   MILLENNIUM BABY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BEDFORD, Texas _ Christine Benton is preparing for a rigorous
race. She has undergone a physical and says she's in good shape.
She's taking plenty of vitamins and even has a uniform picked out.
But unlike an Olympian hoping to bring home a medal in 2000,
Benton's trophy would be swaddled in a soft blanket. Benton, 32, of
Haltom City wants to have a baby on Jan. 1, 2000. So she and her
husband will be off and running on Friday _ the day given by
obstetricians and gynecologists as the ideal day to conceive a baby
to be born on Jan. 1. By TERRY LEE GOODRICH. Story has moved in
``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
