<P>
   OFFICE POLITICS-BOOK &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ As someone who has always been a chronic sufferer of
foot-in-mouth disease, I can't say how much I wish Ronna
Lichtenberg's new book had come across my desk sooner. ``Work Would
Be Great If It Weren't for All the People'' ($12.95, Hyperion) is
subtitled ``Making Office Politics Work for You.'' And while
Lichtenberg comes from the kind of cubicled corporate world that
Dilbert calls home _ she's a former senior vice president at
Prudential Securities and now runs a marketing and strategy
consulting firm _ she manages to cram in information relevant to
almost any office environment. By TODD CAMP. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
