   DELL _ AUSTIN, Texas _ At its spring meeting with analysts in
New York, Dell officials say they'll continue to build on Dell's
fledgling relationship with IBM, but stop short of confirming some
analysts' speculation that it will take over IBM's personal
computer business. In the short term, they say, Dell will continue
to expand its personal computer business, server business and to a
lesser extent, its service business to continue to grow at rates
that are better than the industry. (Mahoney, Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   DELTA _ ATLANTA _ Delta Air Lines is ``On Top of the World'' no
more. It is jettisoning its advertising tagline after only two
years and will roll out a new one this fall. ``It just didn't have
any connection,'' said Martin White, new vice president for
consumer marketing. ``The customers didn't understand it and the
employees didn't buy into it. We're not upset that it had a short
life because it didn't work.'' (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
