   ASA _ ATLANTA _ Atlantic Southeast Airlines starts Canadair
Regional Jet service from Atlanta to Daytona Beach and Melbourne,
Fla., and Islip, NY, and expands its schedule to Augusta,
Montgomery and Tallahassee this summer. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHWIRE _ ATLANTA _ Southwire Co., one of the world's largest
manufacturers of wire and cable, will sell its copper-refining
division in Carrollton, Ga., and its strike-plagued
aluminum-smelting division in Hawesville, Ky. No buyer has been
found for either division. Southwire's copper refinery, Copper
Division Southwire, employs about 380 people, while its
aluminum-smelting division has about 800 workers. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUSTRALIA-COKE _ Australian antitrust authorities have blocked
Coca-Cola's acquisition of Cadbury-Sweppes' operations, but a new
proposal is in the works. Meanwhile, Mexican authorities still are
weighing whether to approve the sale there. The stock is up in
early trading. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   CONCOURS _ AMELIA ISLAND, Fla. _ Highlights from annual concours
d'elegance at Amelia Island. (Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: Sidebar column.
</P>
<P>
   NCR-SMARTMICROWAVE _ Taking a page from George Orwell's 1984,
NCR Corp. has developed a trash can and a microwave oven that will
keep track of what you consume, when you cook it and when you throw
the container away. The appliances will generate a shopping list
for you and then relay all the information via the Internet to
retailers who can then tailor coupons and special offers based on
your consumption patterns. And the trash can will sort your
recyclables for you too. And your microwave oven can surf the
Internet and transfer funds between bank accounts for you.
(Bischoff, Dayton Daily News). MOVED
</P>
