 &UR; STREET  &LR; - (column) Is there anything fundamentally wrong with
fledgling Internet sites that offer shares of their companies to
people who sign up on their Web sites?
</P>
<P>
   Not really. There doesn't appear to be any tangible downside for
consumers who hold the shares, except that they may never be worth
the paper on which their printed.
