stature. I have what doctors refer to as infant-adult condition. At
3 feet and 55 pounds, I have the bone mass and muscle tissue of a
small child. I'm having trouble finding work with a real estate
brokerage in my town. One broker said she could not hire me because
I would be viewed by potential buyers as ``a small infant'' (her
words) and would not be able to gain the respect necessary to
represent the company. How can I find a brokerage that will see me
as more than just a little person? By Ilana DeBare
</P>
