<HEADLINE>
TWO MORE OF SEVEN SURVIVING OCTUPLETS RELEASED FROM HOSPITAL &HT;    
 &HT;    
 &HT;    
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  c. 1999 Houston Chronicle 
<TEXT>
 &QL;
<P>
   HOUSTON _ Two more of the seven surviving octuplets were
discharged Thursday from the hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Chidi and Chima, both girls, went home with their parents, Nkem
Chukwu and Iyke Louis Udobi, at 3 p.m. The 14-week-old infants
joined sisters Ebuka and Echerem and brother Jioke, who were
discharged March 3, at the family's southwest Houston home.
</P>
<P>
   Ikem and Gorom remain listed in serious condition at Texas
Children's Hospital. The parents say they will be released later
this month.
</P>
<P>
   The firstborn, Ebuka, was delivered Dec. 8. Seven more babies
were born Dec. 20. The smallest of the eight, Odera, did not
develop lungs as fully as the others and died a week later.
</P>
<P>
   XXXX END OF STORY
</P>
