<P>
   CHINA-WHEAT (Washington) _ In a major victory for the
Northwest's struggling farmers, China agrees to drop its 27-year
ban on the importation of wheat. The agreement, which Chinese
Premier Zhu Rongji and President Clinton announce at a joint news
conference, is greeted with jubilation by wheat farmers and elected
officials who have been jealously eying China's 1 billion consumers
as a potential market.
