<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-SCI-ASPERGERS-SYNDROME-NYT (moved on Monday, Apr. 5)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Apr. 5,
about a form of autism called Asperger's syndrome misstated the
name of a branch of the National Institutes of Health that has
collected data on the condition. It is the National Institute of
Child Health and Human Development, not Child Health and Mental
Development.
</P>
