A1363 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-LAKERS-LADN     04-08 0318
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LAKERS' PATH GETS TOUGHER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Several weeks and several upheavals ago, the
Lakers' goals were clear: Win the Pacific Division, capture the top
seed in the conference, gain home-court advantage throughout the
playoffs, win a championship.
</P>
<P>
   The last objective is still attainable, but the route to the NBA
Finals will probably be tougher because the other items on the list
are nearly out of reach.
</P>
<P>
   As of Thursday, with 13 games to go in a compact season that has
evaporated in a flash, the Lakers were five games behind Portland
in the Pacific, fifth overall in the West and still battling to
gain even one round of home-court advantage in the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   But failing to win top seeding won't necessarily be considered a
failure, Kobe Bryant said.
</P>
<P>
   ``Yeah and no. That was our ultimate goal and it still is a
goal. But to get to that in the first place, the main thing we
constantly said is you have to improve to get there. You have to
take it one day at a time and that's what we're trying to do,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
   ``You wanna be in front, don't get me wrong. If we could trade
spots and say we'd be at the top spot and have home-court advantage
throughout the playoffs, that'd be great.''
</P>
<P>
   It's not entirely out of reach. The Lakers will have a virtual
mini-playoff with Portland to decide Pacific Division supremacy, as
they face the Trail Blazers four times in the last 11 games,
starting Tuesday at the Rose Garden.
</P>
<P>
   ``What we're trying to do is play to improve, play to get
better,'' Bryant said. ``We're not even close to playing our best
basketball. But we're still in the hunt, we're still in the race,
we're still playing good basketball.... Like I said, just continue
to learn. It's fun, going through a trial process. It's all
good.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
